I"<p>Cablegram 473 LONDON, 25 June 1940, 9.28 p.m.</p>

<p>FOR THE PRIME MINISTER MOST SECRET</p>

<p>Attitude to Petain Government in suspense pending development re alternative authority which more promising, Reynaud [1] and Campinchi [2] having declared intention of coming to England unless alternative Government set up in French colonial empire.</p>

<p>Gort [3] and Duff Cooper [4] left by air this morning to contact them at Perpignan and then proceed together to Morocco. This development may meet objection in paragraph 3 of 466. [5] Mittelhauser [6] in Syria has declared will take no orders from the Bordeaux Government and appears to have the support of troops.</p>

<p>BRUCE</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 French Prime Minister until 16 June 1940.</p>

<p>2 French Minister of Marine until 16 June 1940.</p>

<p>3 Commander-in-Chief, British Field Force.</p>

<p>4 U.K. Minister of Information.</p>

<p>5 Document 432.</p>

<p>6 Commander-in-Chief of French forces in the Middle East.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p><em>[FA: A3195, 1.4710]</em></p>
